{{About|the ''Wehrmacht'' officer|the English music critic, author and teacher of singing|Herman Klein}} {{Infobox military person |name=Hermann Klein |birth_date=19 July 1913 |death_date={{death date and age|1944|8|18|1913|7|19|df=y}} [[Missing in action|MIA]] |birth_place=[[Willich]], German Empire |death_place=[[Ērgļi]], Courland |image= |caption= |nickname= |allegiance={{flag|Nazi Germany}} |branch=[[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] |serviceyears= |rank=[[Major (Germany)|Major]] of the [[Military reserve force|Reserves]] (posthumously) |commands= |unit=329th Infantry Division |battles=[[World War II]] |awards=[[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves]] |laterwork= }} '''Hermann Klein''' (19 July 1913 – 18 August 1944) was a [[Major (Germany)|Major]] of the [[Military reserve force|Reserves]] in the Wehrmacht during World War II. He was also a recipient of the [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves]]. The Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross and its higher grade Oak Leaves was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership.
==Awards== *[[Iron Cross]] (1939) ** 2nd Class (3 November 1941)<ref name="Thomas p373">Thomas 1997, p. 373.</ref> ** 1st Class (14 February 1943)<ref name="Thomas p373"/> *[[Honour Roll Clasp of the Army]] (17 December 1943)<ref name="Thomas p373"/> *[[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves]] **Knight's Cross on 15 April 1944 as ''[[Oberleutnant]]'' of the Reserves and ''Regimentsadjutant'' in the Grenadier-Regiment 551<ref>Fellgiebel 2000, p. 258.</ref>{{refn|According to Scherzer as adjutant of Grenadier-Regiment 551.<ref name="Scherzer p446">Scherzer 2007, p. 446.</ref>|group="Note"}} **567th Oak Leaves on 2 September 1944 as ''Hauptmann'' of the Reserves and ''Regimentsadjutant'' in the Grenadier-Regiment 551<ref name="Scherzer p446"/><ref>Fellgiebel 2000, p. 87.</ref>
